image_analysis.description: A photograph of the interior of a closet. The closet contains a gold-colored hanging rod with several empty wooden and plastic hangers on the right side. On the left, a metal drying rack or shelving unit holds folded white linens or towels. Additional white towels are stacked on a shelf above the rod. On the floor of the closet, there is a stack of white styrofoam containers, possibly coolers or shipping containers. The floor is covered in tan or gold-colored carpeting. A white door with a brass-colored knob is visible on the right edge of the frame.
image_analysis.layout: Interior shot of a storage space/closet.

stamps_or_markings: Bates stamp 'EFTA00001164' in bottom right corner

document_metadata.subject: Interior of a closet with linens and containers

notes: The photograph appears to be an evidentiary photo from an investigation, indicated by the Bates stamp. The styrofoam containers on the floor have some embossed text that is mostly illegible, though one appears to say 'NATURE'S' or similar.
